A railway station in Zhangjiakou, North China's Hebei Province, is seen under construction on Wednesday. The railway link between Beijing and Zhangjiakou is one of the vital projects for the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympic Games. Construction started in 2016 and the line is scheduled to open for traffic in December 2019. Travel time will be cut from 3 hours 12 minutes to about 50 minutes. Photo: VCG Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Utah celebrates 150th birthday of Transcontinental RailroadActress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame star